      "note": "Lit., \"a time computed [by Us]\", i.e., the Day of Judgment: a reference to the last sentence of verse 3 above, where the Prophet is made to say, \"I dread for you the suffering [which is bound to befall you] on that awesome Day!\" Among the several meanings which the noun ummah comprises, that of \"time\" or \"a period of time\" is the most appropriate here (Zamakhshari, Ibn Kathir and other classical commentators)."
