      "note_no": "15",
      "note": "Lit., \"that which they were wont to deride enfolded them (haqa bihim)\". According to almost all the commentators, the use of the past tense in the verb haqa, despite the fact that it refers to the future, has the syntactic value of a stress, implying the inevitability of the happening to which it relates. (See also note 9 on 6:10.)"
